snippet.textDisplay: Mai Dhai ne kamaal kar diya. Typical Rajasthani folk song in Marwadi dialect of border area.(Barmer,Jaisalmer,Bikaner) Meaning - When will you come to our land(country), we are eagerly waiting for you. Tears are rolling down from my eyes. I am from that area of Rajasthan. Beautiful rendition by both singers. Cultures have no borders/boundaries. Feel very proud of my Rajputana Culture.Brilliant music by Coke Studio. Pakistan ke funkaaron ka Sukria. Best Wishes.   Milapchand Jain
snippet.textOriginal: Mai Dhai ne kamaal kar diya. Feel very proud of my Rajputana Culture.Brilliant music by Coke Studio. Pakistan ke funkaaron ka Sukria. Best Wishes.   Milapchand Jain
